This paper deals with the capacity region of a communication system with secret key authentication, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the adversary's control over the channel, which falls under the category of communication and information theory (cs.CC). The use of secret keys and authentication also relates to multimedia security (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.SI).
